<br>
Druids.  Druids are lazy.  I would be happy as hell if my guild needed more druids and I could switch back... I wouldn't think twice about it... I would never look back.<br>
<br>
You have NO idea how hard it is to be a bard until you have played one.. and played it CORRECTLY.<br>
<br>
Lets start off with a couple comparisons.<br>
<br>
During combat how many times to you switch your primary hand weapon?<br>
<br>
Druids = 0<br>
Bards = 2-3 times<br>
<br>
How many times to you hit a spell gem in a  period of 9 seconds?<br>
<br>
Druids = 2<br>
Bards = 6<br>
<br>
Last but not least in a 20 min game cycle how many right clicks will you have to do on equipment?  Assume 1 mob per minute.<br>
<br>
Druids (after new DoT stacking and epic snare removal) = 20.<br>
Bards = 26<br>
<br>
When a mob is pulled to the group how close to you hav eto stay to the mob and how often do you have to move to keep in range?<br>
<br>
Druids = maybe once<br>
Bards = Constantly<br>
<br>
Now... with that out of the way... how can 1 ignorant druid betray his whole class with one post based off of pure stupidity?  You sound like a complete jackass... basing your opinion about a class you don't even really play.<br>
